article_title: U.N.’s Amano Says Iran Nuclear Probe Will Be Ready Mid-December
article_text:
The head of the United Nations atomic energy agency said Monday he believes the probe into Iran’s past nuclear activities will be wrapped up on time by mid-December, even though he acknowledged “much work” still needs doing to shed light on Tehran’s past actions.

In comments at a news conference in Vienna, International Atomic Energy Agency Director-General Yukiya Amano noted that Iran had met its Aug. 15 deadline to provide written explanations on its past nuclear work, which many western officials say was aimed at...
